**`ExercisePreviewRow`** — used on the Home screen's today workout section
Path: `/Users/viniciuscarvalho/Documents/FitToday/FitToday/FitToday/Presentation/Features/Home/Components/ExercisePreviewRow.swift`

```swift
struct ExercisePreviewRow: View {
    let exerciseName: String
    let imageURL: URL?
    let setsAndReps: String
    let muscleGroup: String?

    var body: some View {
        HStack {
            CachedAsyncImage(url: imageURL, placeholder: Image(systemName: "dumbbell.fill"), ...)
            Text(exerciseName)   // passed in as a plain String
            Text(setsAndReps)
        }
    }
}
```

**`GeneratedExerciseRow`** — used in the AI-generated workout preview sheet
Path: `/Users/viniciuscarvalho/Documents/FitToday/FitToday/FitToday/Presentation/Features/Home/Views/GeneratedWorkoutPreview.swift`

```swift
struct GeneratedExerciseRow: View {
    let exercise: GeneratedExercise
    var body: some View {
        Text(exercise.name)   // no image thumbnail at the row level
        Label(exercise.targetMuscle, systemImage: "figure.strengthtraining.traditional")
        Label(exercise.equipment, systemImage: "dumbbell")
    }
}
```
No image is shown in the row. The detail sheet (`ExerciseDetailSheet`) also uses a placeholder rectangle — no real image loading here.

---

### 2. Workout Preview/Detail Views

**`WorkoutPreviewView`** — preview before starting a WGER program workout
Path: `/Users/viniciuscarvalho/Documents/FitToday/FitToday/FitToday/Presentation/Features/Workout/Views/WorkoutPreviewView.swift`

Uses `ExercisePreviewCard` (private) which shows `exercise.imageURL` via `ExerciseMediaImageURL`, plus `exercise.name` as a plain string from `ProgramExercise.name` (which delegates to `wgerExercise.name`).

**`ProgramWorkoutDetailView`** — detail/edit screen for a WGER program workout
Path: `/Users/viniciuscarvalho/Documents/FitToday/FitToday/FitToday/Presentation/Features/Programs/Views/ProgramWorkoutDetailView.swift`

Uses `ExerciseRowCard` (shown above). Contains complete `Wger category ID -> MuscleGroup` and equipment mapping logic, duplicated from `WorkoutPreviewView`.

**`ExerciseExecutionCard`** — full-screen card shown during active workout execution
Path: `/Users/viniciuscarvalho/Documents/FitToday/FitToday/FitToday/Presentation/Features/Workout/Components/ExerciseExecutionCard.swift`

```swift
if let media = prescription.exercise.media, let mediaURL = media.bestMediaURL {
    ExerciseMediaImageURL(
        url: mediaURL,
        size: CGSize(width: UIScreen.main.bounds.width - 80, height: 240),
        contentMode: .fit
    )
}
Text(prescription.exercise.name)
    .font(FitTodayFont.display(size: 24, weight: .bold))
```

---

### 3. Image Loading

**`ExerciseMediaImageURL`** — the main reusable image loader
Path: `/Users/viniciuscarvalho/Documents/FitToday/FitToday/FitToday/Presentation/DesignSystem/ExerciseMediaImage.swift`

- Uses a custom `@Observable ExerciseMediaLoader` class (not `AsyncImage`)
- Two-tier cache: `ImageCacheService` (persistent) first, then `NSCache` in-memory
- Detects GIF content by MIME type, URL extension, or magic bytes (`GIF87a`/`GIF89a`)
- GIFs are rendered via `WKWebView` (`ExerciseGIFWebView`) to support animation
- Static images are decoded with `UIImage(data:)` and displayed as `Image(uiImage:)`
- Fallback: `figure.strengthtraining.traditional` system icon

**`ExerciseThumbnail`** — wrapper for small list thumbnails, delegates to `ExerciseMediaImageURL`

```swift
struct ExerciseThumbnail: View {
    let media: ExerciseMedia?
    var size: CGFloat = 50
    // prefers imageURL, falls back to gifURL
    private var mediaURL: URL? { media?.imageURL ?? media?.gifURL }
}
```

**`ExerciseHeroImage`** — wrapper for large detail screens, prefers GIF over image (opposite priority from thumbnail)

**`CachedAsyncImage`** — used only in `ExercisePreviewRow`. Goes through the `ImageCacheService` environment, with a `ProgressView` spinner while loading.

**`ExerciseGifThumbnail`** (in `ExerciseRowView`) — uses bare `AsyncImage` with no caching. This is an outlier in the codebase.

---

### 4. Exercise Name Source and Language (WGER)

Path: `/Users/viniciuscarvalho/Documents/FitToday/FitToday/FitToday/Domain/Entities/WgerModels.swift`

The `WgerExercise` struct carries a single `name: String` field already resolved for a specific language. There is NO dynamic language resolution at display time in the UI views.

Language resolution happens upstream in `WgerExerciseInfo.name(for:)`:
```swift
func name(for languageId: Int) -> String {
    // Try preferred language first
    if let translation = translations.first(where: { $0.language == languageId }) {
        return translation.name
    }
    // Fall back to English (language ID 2)
    if let english = translations.first(where: { $0.language == 2 }) {
        return english.name
    }
    return translations.first?.name ?? "Exercise \(id)"
}
```

The app targets Portuguese (`WgerLanguageCode.portuguese = 4`) as default. Language ID `2` = English. Exercise names from WGER are resolved to Portuguese first, then English as fallback, at the repository/service layer before reaching the UI. All views simply read `exercise.name` or `wgerExercise.name` — a pre-resolved string.

---

### 5. Domain Models

**`ProgramWorkout` / `ProgramExercise`**
Path: `/Users/viniciuscarvalho/Documents/FitToday/FitToday/FitToday/Domain/Entities/ProgramWorkout.swift`

```swift
struct ProgramWorkout: Identifiable, Hashable, Sendable {
    let id: String
    let templateId: String
    let title: String
    let subtitle: String
    let estimatedDurationMinutes: Int
    let exercises: [ProgramExercise]
}

struct ProgramExercise: Identifiable, Hashable, Sendable {
    let id: String
    let wgerExercise: WgerExercise   // raw WGER API response embedded directly
    let sets: Int
    let repsRange: ClosedRange<Int>
    let restSeconds: Int
    let notes: String?
    var order: Int

    var name: String { wgerExercise.name }          // computed from WGER
    var imageURL: URL? { ... wgerExercise.mainImageURL }
    var allImageURLs: [URL] { wgerExercise.imageURLs.compactMap { URL(string: $0) } }
}
```

Image URLs are absolute URLs pointing to `https://wger.de/media/exercise-images/...`.

**`WgerExercise`** (raw API model)
Path: `/Users/viniciuscarvalho/Documents/FitToday/FitToday/FitToday/Domain/Entities/WgerModels.swift`

Key fields: `name: String`, `mainImageURL: String?` (JSON key `"main_image"`), `imageURLs: [String]` (JSON key `"images"`), `language: Int?`, `category: Int?`, `muscles: [Int]`, `equipment: [Int]`.

---

### Summary

| Context | Component | Name Source | Image Loading |
|---|---|---|---|
| Workout plan view / execution | `WorkoutExerciseRow`, `PhaseSectionView` | `prescription.exercise.name` (WorkoutExercise) | `ExerciseThumbnail` -> `ExerciseMediaImageURL` (custom caching) |
| Active workout card | `ExerciseExecutionCard` | `prescription.exercise.name` | `ExerciseMediaImageURL` (full-size, GIF support) |
| Program workout detail | `ExerciseRowCard` (in ProgramWorkoutDetailView) | `exercise.name` -> `wgerExercise.name` | `ExerciseMediaImageURL` (circle crop) |
| Workout preview before start | `ExercisePreviewCard` (in WorkoutPreviewView) | `exercise.name` -> `wgerExercise.name` | `ExerciseMediaImageURL` |
| Home today section | `ExercisePreviewRow` | `exerciseName: String` (passed in) | `CachedAsyncImage` |
| Custom workout builder | `ExerciseRowView` | `exercise.exerciseName` (CustomExerciseEntry) | Bare `AsyncImage` (no caching) |
| AI-generated workout | `GeneratedExerciseRow` | `exercise.name` (GeneratedExercise) | No image shown |

