The views use `.specializations` as a non-optional (e.g., `.isEmpty`, `.prefix(2)`) but I've made it return `[String]?` via computed property. This will cause compile errors.

I need to update the views OR change the computed property to return `[String]` (non-optional, defaulting to empty array). The simpler fix is to change the computed properties to return non-optional defaults:

```swift
var bio: String? { profile?.bio }
var specializations: [String] { profile?.specializations ?? [] }
var city: String? { profile?.city }
var maxStudents: Int? { profile?.maxStudents }


```

This way the views don't need to change.

